## 0. Thesis

V4 was built toward a thing it could not yet hold: a typed object
whose value carries its own exact truth. Its status calculus,
multi-field validity, `ConditioningStatus`, and "is-this-small /
proven-zero / below-detection" apparatus (Axioms 6–7) are V4 typing
numerical truth **without** the exact account — coarse proxies for
what the ledger now answers in ℚ. Cella is that object, held and
proven: **value + account == TRUE in ℚ** (HR132–134), portable to the
integer substrate (HR136) and to several variables (HR137).

**The inversion:** make the account the **ground truth** and re-derive
V4's apparatus as projections of it. Status becomes a readout of the
account; conditioning becomes exact exposure; smallness and zero
become ledger queries; metrology becomes the honest boundary where the
exact account hands off to enclosure-or-refusal. **Nothing is
discarded. Each layer is re-grounded on the exact thing it was
approximating, and sharpened in the re-seating.**

This is a *re-founding*, not a teardown. V4's working substrate stays
load-bearing until each piece is re-seated and verified. The center of
gravity moves to the account; the engine keeps running throughout.

## 1. What stays beneath the trunk (the taproot has a root)

Axiom 12 (self-derivation) demands Cella derive from something — and
it does. Beneath the Cella trunk sits the **minimal IEEE floor**: the
bedrock typed atoms (`typed_value`, the correctly-rounded IEEE
operations) and the error-free transforms the account is built on. The
tree is *Cella-on-the-IEEE-floor*, not Cella floating free. The floor
is not re-founded; it is the parent the trunk registers against
(Axiom 11's epistemic stance and the IEEE-mandated atom allowances
stay bedrock).

