5. **The engine stays alive.** No layer is removed before its
   re-seated replacement passes its gate and the consumers above it
   are re-pointed. At every commit, the suite is green.

## 3. The load-bearing design question (resolved IN the taproot stage, not here)

Where does the account live in the layer stack — is the Cella object a
**Layer-1 primitive result type** (every primitive op returns
value+account natively), or a **Layer-2 composed object** that
decorates operations? This fork shapes everything downstream. It is
**not pre-decided in this charter**; it is the first thing the taproot
stage resolves, under plan-mode + brainstorming, from the actual code.

## 4. STAGE 1 — the taproot (the only stage scoped here)

**Goal:** harden Cella into a substrate-grade foundation — the typed
account result type plus the native rational-op set — so the tree can
be re-rooted on it. Until this exists, the inversion has nothing to
stand on (you cannot root a tree on an eval-tier object).

**Scope.**
- A **typed account result type** (the Cella object as a first-class
  `TypedResult`): value + residue ledger + exposure channels (per-
  variable / coupling / const, per HR137) + status-as-projection. Full
  core integration — status family registered, validity, conditioning
  *derived from exposure*, provenance, protocol surface.
- The **native rational-op set carried account-first**: add, sub, mul,
  div, pow (integer), neg, abs — each emitting the account natively,
  with the float64 and integer (Arm I) substrates as the first two
  carriers of one fold law.
- Through the **§4 dissection gate** (constants measured; theorems as
  registered transitions; bit-match or documented divergence;
  modelling commitments declared) and the **eval-tier registry →
  atomic promotion** path (F13 / Option B).

**New ground, flagged honestly.** The prior promotions (`typed_log`,
`exp`/`pow`/`sin`, 2026-06-07) returned bespoke dataclasses and thereby
*sidestepped* the full TypedResult lineage/registration gates. The
account primitive will be the **first true account-carrying TypedResult
promotion** — `EVAL_TIER_PROMOTED` is empty today. This is the genuine
unknown; the taproot stage derisks it for everything after.

**The superseded artifact, absorbed not lost.** `difference_tower/
expr.py` is hard-univariate (single token `"x"`); Arm M already built
its replacement (`mexpr.py`, the n-variable expression class). The
taproot adopts `mexpr` as the expression model and retires `expr` to
the closed difference-tower record — a supersession, not a loss.

**Stage-1 exit criteria.**
1. The account primitive exists at substrate calibre, IEEE taproot
   beneath it, passing every gate; suite green.
2. The §3 placement question is resolved with its rationale recorded.
3. **Proof-of-concept of "nothing lost":** the axioms most directly
   implicated (5 "representation is a path"; 6 "zero is measured or
   proven") re-derived as readouts of the account, entered in the §5
   ledger. This is the inversion validated on its first contact, before
   any further layer is touched.

**Stop at the stage report + a re-seating draft** for Will's sign-off —
the same checkpoint discipline the arms ran under.

